Not too thrilled with the value of a Groupon from Sports Pub.
To be clear...  Service was very personable (Alyssa), but sporadic.
This is an indication of a section that is too large for the server.
I believe she had every table outside the bar on a Saturday night, albeit early (approx 6pm).
I have an issue with the Groupon that I purchased.
If I pay $14 for a buy-one-get-one, I expect to receive $14 in savings.
That was not the case.
Because of our selections, the savings only priced out to about $6 less than had I just walked in.
In fact, I am not sure it is possible to receive $14 in savings given the limitations of the sandwich menu and domestic beer selections.
As an aside, I wouldn't just walk in because this place is across town from me..  To be clear, we also ordered an appetizer, soft drink, and craft beer.
I didn't want to give the impression that we were there to redeem the Groupon, drop a gratuity, and leave.
The food was standard bar food.
The chicken nachos were ho-hum.
The sandwiches were tasty.

